  "local_port": 42996,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I make homemade pancakes without baking soda?",
  "response": "Making pancakes without baking soda is definitely possible! You can use baking powder instead, or rely on other ingredients for leavening. Here\u2019s a simple recipe for homemade pancakes that doesn\u2019t require baking soda:\n\n### Simple Pancake Recipe (No Baking Soda)\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 cup all-purpose flour\n- 2 teaspoons baking powder\n- 1 tablespoon sugar (optional)\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 1 cup milk (or milk alternative)\n- 1 large egg\n- 2 tablespoons melted butter or vegetable oil\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract (optional)\n\n**Instructions:**\n\n1. **Mix Dry Ingredients**: In a large mixing bowl, whisk together the flour, baking powder, sugar, and salt.\n\n2. **Mix Wet Ingredients**: In another bowl, beat the egg, then add the milk, melted butter (or oil), and vanilla extract. Mix until well combined.\n\n3. **Combine Mixtures**: Pour the wet ingredients into the dry ingredients. Stir gently until just combined. Be careful not to overmix; a few lumps are okay.\n\n4. **Heat the Pan**: Preheat a non-stick skillet or griddle over medium heat. You can lightly grease with butter or oil if desired.\n\n5. **Cook the Pancakes**: Pour about 1/4 cup of batter for each pancake onto the heated skillet. Cook until bubbles form on the surface and the edges look set, about 2-3 minutes. Flip and cook for another 1-2 minutes until golden brown.\n\n6. **Serve**: Remove the pancakes from the skillet and serve warm with your favorite toppings like syrup, fruit, or whipped cream.\n\n### Tips:\n- If you want fluffier pancakes without baking soda, you could try separating the egg, whipping the egg whites to peaks, and folding them into the batter at the end.\n- For added flavor, you can incorporate ingredients like cinnamon, mashed bananas, or chocolate chips into the batter.\n\nEnjoy your homemade pancakes!",
